HEADWORD: Sarment
<hw>Sar"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sarmentum</ets> a twig, fr. <ets>sarpere</ets> to cut off, to trim:
cf. F. <ets>sarment</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A prostrate
filiform stem or runner, as of the strawberry. See
<er>Runner</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sarmentaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
